race.comment: ALLY (3) is back after a five-month spell for the Munce stable. Finished less than a length from the winner when she opened last prep at the Sunshine Coast. At her best over today's journey so this looks a great chance to break a 60-week win drought. MUSIC FEVER (11) put the writing on the wall last start when she closed well but found one better over this course and distance. Rock hard fit after three runs back and from a good gate gets every chance. STATEMENT OF TRUTH (15) is a lightly raced three-year-old back from a 114-day lay-off. Has been in the money at both previous first-up runs. Two recent trials should have him right up to the mark. INQUISITOR (7) has a terrible gate to overcome. Recent efforts have been sound so with a bit of luck he should be in the finish. ON POINT PIXIE (6) disappointed at the Gold Coast last time but this is her preferred trip so watch for a better performance.
